         <h1 class="rssTitle">
          World Nuclear News
         </h1>
         <div class="feed rssfeed">
          <h2>
           <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/WR-US-project-to-recycle-naval-fuel-gets-Senate-approval-2206188.html">
            US project to recycle naval fuel gets Senate approval
           </a>
          </h2>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Published
           </strong>
           : Fri, 22 Jun 2018 16:06:58 GMT
          </p>
          <p>
           The US Senate has approved a proposal for a USD15 million pilot programme to recycle used naval nuclear fuel for use as fuel in advanced nuclear reactors. The proposal - an amendment to the fiscal 2019 Energy and Water Appropriations Bill - was adopted by the full Senate by 87 votes to 9.
          </p>
          <br/>
          <h2>
           <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/WR-Approval-for-decommissioning-of-Swiss-reactor-2206185.html">
            Approval for decommissioning of Swiss reactor
           </a>
          </h2>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Published
           </strong>
           : Fri, 22 Jun 2018 15:57:35 GMT
          </p>
          <p>
           <img align="left" alt="Muehleberg NPP - 48" src="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/uploadedImages/wnn/Images/Muehleberg%20NPP%20-%2048.jpg" style="BORDER-TOP-COLOR: ; BORDER-LEFT-COLOR: ; BORDER-BOTTOM-COLOR: ; BORDER-RIGHT-COLOR: ; align: left" title="Muehleberg NPP - 48"/>
           Swiss utility BKW has been issued with a decommissioning order for the Mhleberg nuclear power plant, which is scheduled to permanently shut down at the end of 2019. The order from the country's Department of the Environment, Transport, Energy and Communication states the decommissioning work must be carried out in accordance with a plan submitted by BKW in 2015.
          </p>
          <br/>
          <h2>
           <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/UF-Tanzania-gets-ready-for-uranium-mining-2206187.html">
            Tanzania gets ready for uranium mining
           </a>
          </h2>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Published
           </strong>
           : Fri, 22 Jun 2018 16:18:04 GMT
          </p>
          <p>
           <img align="left" alt="Mkuju_River_env_sampling_(Banzi-TAEC)-48" src="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/uploadedImages/wnn/Images/Mkuju River sampling (IAEA) 48.jpg" title="Mkuju_River_env_sampling_(Banzi-TAEC)-48"/>
           The Tanzanian government has worked actively to implement International Atomic Energy Agency recommendations to develop the legal and regulatory infrastructure ready for uranium mining to commence, the Tanzania Atomic Energy Commission's Dennis Mwalongo said ahead of the IAEA's URAM-2018 symposium.
          </p>
          <br/>
          <h2>
           <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/NN-Chinese-AP1000s-pass-commissioning-milestones-2206184.html">
            Chinese AP1000s pass commissioning milestones
           </a>
          </h2>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Published
           </strong>
           : Fri, 22 Jun 2018 14:55:19 GMT
          </p>
          <p>
           <img align="left" alt="Sanmen 1-2 - 48" src="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/uploadedImages/wnn/Images/Sanmen 1-2 - 48.jpg" title="Sanmen 1-2 - 48"/>
           The start of power generation by two AP1000 reactors under construction in China moved a step closer yesterday with first criticality being achieved at Sanmen 1 and the loading of fuel beginning at Haiyang 1. Both units are expected to start up by the end of this year, becoming the first operating AP1000 reactors.
          </p>
          <br/>
          <h2>
           <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/RS-Darlington-to-supply-molybdenum-99-2106187.html">
            Darlington to supply molybdenum-99
           </a>
          </h2>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Published
           </strong>
           : Thu, 21 Jun 2018 16:23:00 GMT
          </p>
          <p>
           <img align="left" alt="BWXT_OPG_Mo99_(BWXT)-48" src="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/uploadedImages/wnn/Images/BWXT_2 48.jpg" title="BWXT_OPG_Mo99_(BWXT)-48"/>
           Ontario Power Generation's Darlington nuclear power plant is to produce molybdenum-99 for use in new technetium-99m generators designed by BWX Technologies Inc. The Candu plant will be the first large-scale commercial nuclear power plant in the world to produce Mo-99.
          </p>
          <br/>
          <h2>
           <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/RS-UK-regulator-reports-on-progress-in-2017-2018-21061801.html">
            UK regulator reports on progress in 2017-2018
           </a>
          </h2>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Published
           </strong>
           : Thu, 21 Jun 2018 15:05:01 GMT
          </p>
          <p>
           The UK's Office for Nuclear Regulation has published its annual report highlighting the extent of its regulatory activities. These included more than 1000 inspections, design acceptance confirmation for a new reactor, ongoing modernisation of its regulations, and its participation in the first European topical peer review on ageing management of nuclear power plants.
          </p>
          <br/>
          <h2>
           <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/NN-Regulator-details-Taishan-1-commissioning-schedule-2106184.html">
            Regulator details Taishan 1 commissioning schedule
           </a>
          </h2>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Published
           </strong>
           : Thu, 21 Jun 2018 13:45:29 GMT
          </p>
          <p>
           <img align="left" alt="Taishan 1 and 2 - November 2017 - 48" src="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/uploadedImages/wnn/Images/Taishan%201%20and%202%20-%20November%202017%20-%2048.jpg" style="" title="Taishan 1 and 2 - November 2017 - 48"/>
           Unit 1 of the Taishan nuclear power plant is expected to be connected to the grid next month and achieve full-power operation by September, according to China's nuclear safety regulator. The unit, which achieved first criticality earlier this month, is expected to become the first EPR reactor to enter commercial operation, which it is scheduled to later this year.
          </p>
          <br/>
          <h2>
           <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/WR-Full-scale-tests-to-start-soon-at-Finnish-repository-2006185.html">
            Full-scale tests to start soon at Finnish repository
           </a>
          </h2>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Published
           </strong>
           : Wed, 20 Jun 2018 15:49:03 GMT
          </p>
          <p>
           <img align="left" alt="Disposal canister - 48" src="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/uploadedImages/wnn/Images/Disposal%20canister%20-%2048.jpg" title="Disposal canister - 48"/>
           Finnish waste management company Posiva said it will soon begin the full-scale final disposal test for used nuclear fuel at the Onkalo underground characterisation facility. The test is designed to demonstrate that the final disposal process will work as planned, a condition for obtaining an operating licence for the repository under construction at Olkiluoto.
          </p>
          <br/>
          <h2>
           <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/NN-GE-Power-starts-Arabelle-production-for-Hinkley-Point-C-20061802.html">
            GE Power starts Arabelle production for Hinkley Point C
           </a>
          </h2>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Published
           </strong>
           : Thu, 21 Jun 2018 09:28:43 GMT
          </p>
          <p>
           <img align="left" alt="Arabelle steam turbine rotor for HPC - 48" src="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/uploadedImages/wnn/Images/Arabelle%20steam%20turbine%20rotor%20for%20HPC%20-%2048.jpg" style="" title="Arabelle steam turbine rotor for HPC - 48"/>
           GE Power's Steam Power and EDF Energy have reached a key project milestone with the start of manufacturing of the first rotor of the Arabelle steam turbine at GE's Belfort, France, centre of excellence for the Hinkley Point C project in England. The contract, awarded in May 2016, is on track to have its first 1770 MWe EPR reactor unit completed by 2025, GE said today.
          </p>
          <br/>
          <h2>
           <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/WR-UK-audit-office-sees-progress-at-Sellafield-20061801.html">
            UK audit office sees progress at Sellafield
           </a>
          </h2>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Published
           </strong>
           : Wed, 20 Jun 2018 15:23:34 GMT
          </p>
          <p>
           Work to reduce risk and high hazard at Sellafield has "taken an encouraging turn for the better", the UK's National Audit Office concludes in a report published today. Sellafield, in northwest England, is the largest and most hazardous nuclear site on the Nuclear Decommissioning Authority estate, accounting for 75% of the long-term cost estimate.
          </p>
          <br/>
